What are Network Types?

A network type tells us how large a network is and where it is used.

Some networks connect just a few devices in one room, while others connect millions of devices across the world.

1. PAN (Personal Area Network)

A PAN is the smallest type of network.

It connects devices around one person, usually within a few meters.

Examples
Mobile ↔ Bluetooth Earbuds
Laptop ↔ Wireless Mouse
Smart Watch ↔ Mobile Phone
